@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy — The Predictions</PageTitle>

<div class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-page__content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: @LastUpdated</p>

        <section>
            <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
            <p>
                The Predictions ("we", "us", "our") is a free, hobby football-prediction game aimed at UK-based players.
                For the purposes of UK data protection law (the UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018) we are the
                data controller for the personal data described in this notice.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you have any questions about this notice or about how we handle your information, please contact us
                at <a href="mailto:antony@thepredictions.co.uk">antony@thepredictions.co.uk</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>2. What information we collect</h2>
            <p>We only collect what we genuinely need to run the game:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account details:</strong> your name, email address, and (optionally) a phone number.</li>
                <li><strong>Authentication data:</strong> a hashed password, or, if you sign in with Google, the limited profile information Google returns to us (name, email, profile picture).</li>
                <li><strong>Gameplay data:</strong> the predictions you submit, the leagues you join, and the boosts you use.</li>
                <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> server logs containing your IP address, browser type, and the actions you take, used for security and debugging.</li>
                <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> we currently set only essential cookies needed to keep you logged in. We do not use advertising or analytics cookies.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3. Why we use it and our lawful basis</h2>
            <p>We process your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Running your account and the game</strong> — including authenticating you, recording your predictions,
                    and showing leaderboards. <em>Lawful basis: performance of a contract</em> (our terms of service with you).
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Transactional emails</strong> — for example, password resets, important changes to a league you have
                    joined, or security notices. <em>Lawful basis: legitimate interest</em> in keeping your account usable and
                    secure, and in some cases performance of a contract.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Optional marketing emails</strong> (for example, news about new features) — only if we add this in
                    future and only after you have opted in. <em>Lawful basis: your consent</em>, which you can withdraw at any time.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Service security and abuse prevention</strong> — for example, reviewing logs after a suspected attack.
                    <em>Lawful basis: legitimate interest</em> in keeping the service safe for everyone.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>4. Who we share it with</h2>
            <p>We do not sell your personal data. We share it only with a small number of trusted service providers who help us run the site:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Microsoft Azure</strong> — hosting and database storage (data stored in the UK / EEA).</li>
                <li><strong>Google</strong> — only if you choose to sign in with Google, in which case Google authenticates you and returns the basic profile information described above.</li>
                <li><strong>Brevo</strong> — sending transactional emails such as password resets.</li>
                <li><strong>Datadog</strong> — collecting application logs and error reports so that we can keep the service running.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We may also disclose your information if we are required to do so by law, or if we need to protect our rights,
                property, or the safety of our users.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>5. International transfers</h2>
            <p>
                Some of the providers above may process limited data outside the UK. Where this happens, we rely on appropriate
                safeguards recognised under UK data protection law (such as the UK International Data Transfer Agreement or
                Addendum, or the EU Standard Contractual Clauses) to keep your information protected.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>6. How long we keep it</h2>
            <p>
                We keep your account information for as long as your account is active. If you ask us to delete your account,
                we will remove or anonymise your personal data within a reasonable period, except where we are required to
                keep certain information for legal, security, or fraud-prevention reasons. Server logs are retained for a
                short, rolling period for operational and security purposes.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
            <p>Under UK data protection law you have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access</strong> a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
                <li><strong>Correct</strong> personal data that is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
                <li><strong>Delete</strong> your personal data ("right to erasure") in certain circumstances.</li>
                <li><strong>Restrict</strong> or <strong>object to</strong> our processing of your personal data in certain circumstances.</li>
                <li><strong>Data portability</strong> — receive a copy of certain data in a machine-readable format.</li>
                <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time where we are relying on your consent (for example, marketing emails).</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                To exercise any of these rights, please email
                <a href="mailto:antony@thepredictions.co.uk">antony@thepredictions.co.uk</a>.
            </p>
            <p>
                You also have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK regulator for data
                protection, at <a href="https://ico.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>. We would, however,
                appreciate the chance to address your concerns first.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>8. Children</h2>
            <p>
                The Predictions is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a child has created an account, please
                contact us and we will take appropriate steps to remove the account.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>9. Changes to this notice</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this notice from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the
                most recent revision. Material changes will be highlighted on the site or by email.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>10. Contact</h2>
            <p>
                Questions, requests, or complaints can be sent to
                <a href="mailto:antony@thepredictions.co.uk">antony@thepredictions.co.uk</a>.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
</div>

@code {
    private const string LastUpdated = "28 April 2026";
}
